e02f0b91-014a-456b-a626-b784d7883d2c.17bf633c-3a0d-4f1a-b1ca-e6be8769b127.description=Description\: 

This step runs the rootpre.sh script in silent mode - if it exists.

Dependencies\: Designed to be run as a privileged system user (typically root).

Return Code\:

0 \= The rootpre.sh script ran successfully.
1 \= At least one error occurred in this step.

Inputs\:
 command - executes ExecuteOracleRootPreScript.py
 Oracle rootpre File - Required\: The fully-qualified pathname of the rootpre.sh file.
 Server Wrapper - Required\: The Jython call wrapper required to run as the machine super user user.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.

 e02f0b91-014a-456b-a626-b784d7883d2c.3545eacc-68b7-49de-a474-78b29a05d702.description=ab7c8229-10f0-467c-a255-8c2a91a92804.cbe901d8-ef9d-448a-8634-a8470f2098de.description e02f0b91-014a-456b-a626-b784d7883d2c.40abd499-d282-4f51-bfd9-ce5630090bd5.description=Description\:
 
 This step will verify the GRID services are online and running if response file was not given CRS_SWONLY parameter. Also will login to ASM and verify the disk group was created and online ready for database(s).
 
 Dependencies\: The step must be run as the instance call wrapper.
 
 Return code\:
 If successful, the step returns a 0. 
 Otherwise, the step returns a 1.

Inputs\:
 command - executes VerifyGridInfrastructureInstallationComplete.py
 ASM Diskgroup List - Required\: Name of the Disk Group List that you are creating. For example\: DATA.
 CRS Binary Stage - Sub-directory of Extract Location used for staging and easy cleanup.
 CRS Home - Required\: The location where the CRS software will be installed.
 Grid Install Option - Required\: The Oracle Grid install option specified in the response file. Valid values are HA_CONFIG or CRS_SWONLY.
 Grid Node List - Optional\: Comma-separated list of the Grid Infrastructure nodes. Must be in the format node1-public\:node1-private\:node1-virtual,node2-public\:node2-private\:node2-virtual.
 Instance Wrapper - Required\: Jython call wrapper to run as the CRS owner.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.
 e02f0b91-014a-456b-a626-b784d7883d2c.4289e3c6-a2bf-4a00-ab41-828f5b102205.description=Description\:
 
This step gathers and validates the advanced parameters for the Provision Grid Infrastructure workflow. 

Dependencies\: Step must be run as the CRS call wrapper.

Return Code\:

0 \= All input parameters are valid.
1 \= Errors occurred while checking input parameters.

Inputs\:
 command - executes GatherAdvancedParametersforProvisionGridInfrastructure.py
 ASM au_size - Optional\: The allocation unit size of the ASM disk group. Valid values are\: 1, 2, 4, 8, 16, 32, or 64 (MB). The default is 1.
 ASM Disk String - Optional\: Value ASM will use to discover the possible ASM Disks
 ASM Redundancy - Optional\: The redundancy level of the ASM disk group. Can be one of the following values\: EXTERNAL for configuring at least 1 ASM disk, NORMAL for configuring at least 3 ASM disks, and HIGH for at least 5 ASM disks. Will be defaulted to EXTERNAL
 Cleanup On Failure - No description
 Cleanup On Success - No description
 CLUSTER - Grid Node List - Optional\: Comma-separated list of the Grid Infrastructure nodes. Must be in the format node1-public\:node1-private\:node1-virtual,node2-public\:node2-private\:node2-virtual.
 CLUSTER - Scan Info - Optional\: The Oracle single Client Access name and port you will use to reference this cluster without specifying a specific node. Example syntax\: sales1-scan.example.net\:1522
 CRS Group - Required\: The system group to be used by the CRS installation. Must be the primary group of the CRS Account User. Typically "oinstall".
 CRS Home Name - Required\: The unique Oracle name for this CRS software install. Must contain only letters, numbers, and underscores (_).
 CRS Name - Required\: The unique Oracle name for this CRS cluster. Must contain only letters, numbers, and dashes (-). The default is RAC01
 CRS Response File - Optional\: An OUI (Oracle Universal Installer) response file for this CRS installation to be downloaded from the software respository. If not specified, a default will be created by the workflow for the installation based on a default template. It will be deleted upon completion.
 CRS User - Required\: The user who will own the CRS software. Typically oracle.
 Download Location - Optional\: The directory to which all downloaded files are copied from the software repository. This is only used if the required files are not found on target server but are found in the software repository.
 Extract Location - Optional\: Directory location where the Oracle database software archives will be extracted. Will be cleaned up at end of workflow execution. If not specified, a default will be created.
 Ignore System Prerequisites - Set to Y to include the -ignoreSysPrereqs parameter when running the install. Valid values are Y, N, and blank. Blank defaults to N.
 Inventory File - Required\: The location of the system's current Oracle inventory file. If it does not exist, it will be created.
 Listener - Optional\: Name and port information of the listener. The syntax is Name\:Port. The default is LISTENER\:1521.
 Network Admin Files - Optional\: Comma-delimited list of files to be downloaded and placed in the CRS_HOME/network/admin directory after the Oracle Software is installed.
 OCR Devices - Required\: The devices CRS uses to store cluster and database configuration information. The device must have the CRS group, be owned by root, and be at least 256Mb. Must be in the same location as Voting Devices.
 runInstaller Parameters - Optional\: Parameters to pass to the Oracle runInstaller command such as -force or -ignoreSysPrereqs.
 Upgrade to Oracle 12 - Optional\: 'True' if upgrading an existing Oracle 11g Grid Infrastructure to Oracle 12 Grid Infrastructure, 'False' otherwise. Default is False.
 Voting Devices - Required\: The devices CRS uses to verify cluster node membership and status. The device must have the CRS owner and group and be at least 256Mb. Must be in the same location as OCR Devices.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 ASM au_size - The allocation unit size of the ASM disk group. Valid values are\: 1, 2, 4, 8, 16, 32, or 64 (MB). The default is 1.
 ASM Disk String - No description
 ASM Redundancy - The redundancy level of the ASM disk group. Can be one of the following values\: EXTERNAL for configuring at least 1 ASM disk, NORMAL for configuring at least 3 ASM disks, and HIGH for at least 5 ASM disks. Will be defaulted to EXTERNAL
 Cleanup On Failure - No description
 Cleanup On Success - No description
 CRS Group - The system group to be used by the CRS installation. Must be the primary group of the CRS Account User. Typically "oinstall".
 CRS Home Name - The unique Oracle name for this CRS software install. Must contain only letters, numbers, and underscores (_).
 CRS Name - The unique Oracle name for this CRS cluster. Must contain only letters, numbers, and dashes (-). The default is RAC01
 CRS Response File - An OUI (Oracle Universal Installer) response file for this CRS installation to be downloaded from the software respository. If not specified, a default will be created by the workflow for the installation based on a default template. It will be deleted upon completion.
 CRS User - The user who will own the CRS software. Typically oracle.
 CRS Wrapper - No description
 Download Location - The location where the files will be downloaded.
 Extract Location - The location where the CRS archive has been (or will be) extracted.
 Grid Node List - Comma-separated list of the Grid Infrastructure nodes. Must be in the format node1-public\:node1-private\:node1-virtual,node2-public\:node2-private\:node2-virtual.
 Ignore System Prerequisites - Set to Y to include the -ignoreSysPrereqs parameter when running the install. Valid values are Y, N, and blank. Blank defaults to N.
 Listener - Name and port information of the listener. The syntax is Name\:Port. The default is LISTENER\:1521.
 Network Admin Files - Comma-delimited list of files to be downloaded and placed in the CRS_HOME/network/admin directory after the Oracle Software is installed.
 OCR Devices - Required\: The devices CRS uses to store cluster and database configuration information. The device must have the CRS group, be owned by root, and be at least 256Mb. Must be in the same location as Voting Devices.
 Oracle Inventory - The location of the system's current Oracle inventory file. If it does not exist, it will be created.
 runInstaller Parameters - Optional\: Parameters to pass to the Oracle runInstaller command such as -force or -ignoreSysPrereqs.
 Scan Info - The Oracle single Client Access name and port you will use to reference this cluster without specifying a specific node. Example syntax\: sales1-scan.example.net\:1522
 Server Wrapper - No description
 Upgrade to Oracle 12 - 'True' if upgrading an existing Oracle 11g Grid Infrastructure to Oracle 12 Grid Infrastructure, 'False' otherwise. Default is False.
 Voting Devices - Required\: The devices CRS uses to verify cluster node membership and status. The device must have the CRS owner and group and be at least 256Mb. Must be in the same location as OCR Devices.
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.
 e02f0b91-014a-456b-a626-b784d7883d2c.5150014e-68fb-4062-bb24-94f3c629373f.description=Description\:
 
 This step runs a series of commands required to complete and verify the Grid Infrastructure silent install. 
 
 Dependencies\: The step must run as the instance call wrapper.
 
 Return code\:
 Upon success, the step returns a 0. 
 Otherwise, the step returns a 1.

Inputs\:
 command - executes RunOracleGridPostInstallCommandsv2.py
 ASM au_size - Required\: The allocation unit size of the ASM disk group. Valid values are\: 1, 2, 4, 8, 16, 32, or 64 (MB).
 ASM Disk String - No description
 ASM Diskgroup List - Required\: List of your diskgroup with their associated disk. Example \: DATA(/dev/raw/raw1,/dev/raw/raw2),FLASH(/dev/raw/raw3)
 ASM Password - Required\: The password used to manage ASM.
 ASM Redundancy - Required\: The redundancy level of the ASM disk group. Can be one of the following values\: EXTERNAL for configuring at least 1 ASM disk, NORMAL for configuring at least 3 ASM disks, and HIGH for at least 5 ASM disks. Will be defaulted to EXTERNAL
 Call Wrapper - Required\: Jython call wrapper required to run as the CRS owner.
 CRS Home - Required\: The location where the CRS software will be installed.
 Grid Install Option - Required\: The Oracle Grid install option specified in the response file. Valid values are HA_CONFIG or CRS_SWONLY.
 Listener - Optional\: Name and port information of the listener. The syntax is Name\:Port. The default is LISTENER\:1521.
 Oracle Inventory - Required\: The location of the system's current Oracle inventory file. If it does not exist, it will be created.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.
 e02f0b91-014a-456b-a626-b784d7883d2c.521d5579-b748-4c0e-82b1-5b4997be1e82.description=Description\:
 
This step gathers and validates the parameters for the Provision Oracle Grid Infrastructure workflow. 

Dependencies\: Step must be run as the CRS call wrapper.

Return Code\:

0 \= All input parameters are valid.
1 \= Errors occurred while checking input parameters.

Inputs\:
 command - executes GatherParametersforProvisionGridInfrastructure.py
 ASM Diskgroup List - Required\: List of your diskgroup with their associated disk. Example \: DATA(/dev/raw/raw1,/dev/raw/raw2),FLASH(/dev/raw/raw3)
 ASM Groups - Required\: Operating system groups that manage ASM. Syntax\: ASMGroup\:ASMDBA\:ASMOper For example\: oinstall\:dba\:asmuser
 ASM Password - Required\: Password for provisioning an Oracle database using ASM storage. The password used to manage ASM.
 CRS Base - Required\: The location of the Oracle Base directory. This is where the admin directory is located.
 CRS Home - Required\: The location where the CRS software will be installed. The default is /u01/app/oracle/product/12.1.0/grid1
 Oracle Software - Required\: The CRS archive(s) (.zip or .cpio.gz) in the software repository.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:

FORM \: DG(,,,),DG(,,)
 ASM Groups - Operating system groups that manage ASM. Syntax\: ASMGroup\:ASMDBA\:ASMOper For example\: oinstall\:dba\:asmuser

 e02f0b91-014a-456b-a626-b784d7883d2c.531c112d-228b-4471-931c-a5bd4d7a0792.description=Description\:
 
 This step runs a series of commands as the root user as specified by the Grid silent install output. 
 
 Dependencies\: The step must run as the server call wrapper.
 
 Return code\:
 
 Upon success, the step returns a 0. 
 Otherwise, the step returns a 1.

Inputs\:
 command - executes RunOracleGridRootPostInstallCommandsv2.py
 Call Wrapper - Required\: Jython call wrapper required to run as the root user.
 CRS Group - Required\: The system group to be used by the CRS installation. Must be the primary group of the CRS Account User. Typically "oinstall".
 CRS Home - Required\: The location where the CRS software will be installed.
 CRS User - Required\: The user who will own the CRS software. Typically "oracle".
 Grid Node List - Required\: Comma-separated list of the CRS nodes. Must be in the format node1-public\:node1-private\:node1-virtual,node2-public\:node2-private\:node2-virtual.
 Installation Command Output - Required\: Output from the CRS installation command. Used to determine what actions to run.
 Upgrade to Oracle 12 - 'True' if upgrading an existing Oracle 11g Grid Infrastructure to Oracle 12 Grid Infrastructure, 'False' otherwise. Default is False.

 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi

 e02f0b91-014a-456b-a626-b784d7883d2c.56c26ca6-ba27-4f3b-b1d0-e4c354821157.description=ab7c8229-10f0-467c-a255-8c2a91a92804.67254b88-ed1e-431e-9d1b-5d6657e8efe0.description e02f0b91-014a-456b-a626-b784d7883d2c.690ae8c5-ce32-462d-93b9-d234f0d931bb.description=Description\:
 
 This step runs the Grid installer in silent mode using the supplied response file. 
 
 Dependencies\: The step must run as the CRS call wrapper.
 
 Return code\:
 Upon success, the step returns a 0. Otherwise, the step returns a 1.

Inputs\:
 command - executes InstallOracleGridInfrastructure.py
 Call Wrapper - Required\: Jython call wrapper required to run as the CRS owner.
 CRS Binary Stage - Required\: The location where the CRS archive has been (or will be) extracted.
 CRS Home Name - Required\: The unique Oracle name for this CRS software install. Must contain only letters, numbers, and underscores (_).
 CRS User - Required\: The user who will own the CRS software. Typically oracle.
 CRS_HOME - Required\: The location where the CRS software will be installed.
 Force Install - Optional\: Set to Y to include the -force parameter when running the install. Valid values are Y, N, and blank.
 Ignore System Prerequisites - Optional\: Set to Y to include the -ignoreSysPrereqs parameter when running the install. Valid values are Y, N, and blank. Blank defaults to N.
 Install Response - Required\: The fully-qualified pathname of the response file to be used by the silent install step.
 Network Admin Files - Optional\: Comma-delimited list of files to be downloaded and placed in the CRS_HOME/network/admin directory after the Oracle Software is installed.
 Oracle Inventory - Required\: The location of the system's current Oracle inventory file. If it does not exist, it will be created.
 runInstaller Parameters - Optional\: Parameters to pass to the Oracle runInstaller command such as -force or -ignoreSysPrereqs.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Installation Command Output - Output from the CRS installation command. Used to determine what actions to run.
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.

Dependencies\: Run as file/directory owner.

Inputs\:

 Call Wrapper - *Required\: The jython call wrapper required to run as the owner of the files/directories.

 Do Not Remove List - *Optional\: List of directories that should not be removed.
 Download File List - *Optional\: List of file downloaded from the Nerve Center
 Download Location - Location temp files were downloaded.
 Temporary File Location - *Optional\: The location where all temporary output files will be placed.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.

 e02f0b91-014a-456b-a626-b784d7883d2c.bfc00396-a26f-4e8d-b424-69afb8715dc4.description=Description\:
 
 This step creates or verifies a response file to silently install Grid Infrastructure for Standalone Server. If the response file is not specified, a generic response file is created. 
 
 Dependencies\: The step must run as the CRS call wrapper.
 
 Return code\:
 
 Upon success, the step returns a 0. 
 Otherwise, the step returns a 1.

Inputs\:
 command - executes VerifyOracleGridInfrastructureResponseFilev2.py
 ASM au_size - Optional\: The allocation unit size of the ASM disk group. Valid values\: 1, 2, 4, 8, 16, 32, or 64 (MB). The default is 1.
 ASM Diskgroup List - Required\: List of your diskgroup with their associated disk. Example \: DATA(/dev/raw/raw1,/dev/raw/raw2),FLASH(/dev/raw/raw3)
 ASM Groups - Required\: Operating system groups that manage ASM. Syntax\: ASMGroup\:ASMDBA\:ASMOper For example\: oinstall\:dba\:asmuser
 ASM Password - Required\: The password used to manage ASM.
 ASM Redundancy - Required\: The redundancy level of the ASM disk group. Valid values are\: EXTERNAL for configuring at least 1 ASM disk, NORMAL for configuring at least 3 ASM disks, and HIGH for at least 5 ASM disks. The default is EXTERNAL.
 Call Wrapper - Required\: Jython call wrapper required to run as the Oracle Instance owner.
 CRS Base - Required\: The location of the Oracle Base directory. This is where the admin directory is located.
 CRS Binary Stage - Required\: The location where the CRS archive has been (or will be) extracted.
 CRS Group - Required\: The system group to be used by the CRS installation. Typically "oinstall".
 CRS Home - Required\: The location where the CRS software will be installed. The default is /u01/app/crs/11.2.0/CRS1
 CRS Home Name - Required\: The unique Oracle name for this CRS software install. Must contain only letters, numbers, and underscores (_).
 CRS Name - Required\: The unique Oracle name for this CRS cluster. Must contain only letters, numbers, and dashes (-).
 CRS Response File - Optional\: An OUI (Oracle Universal Installer) response file for this CRS installation to be downloaded from the software respository. If not specified, a default will be created by the workflow for the installation based on a default template. It will be deleted upon completion.
 Current Node - Required\: The node in the CRS Nodes list that HP DMA is currently running against. For example\: nodex-public\:nodex-private\:nodex-virtual
 GNS Info - Optional\: Grid Naming Service (GNS) information. Format\: three colon-separated fields\: "GNS Subdomain"\:"GNS Virtual IP Address"\:"Configure Cluster Node VIP". Not supported at this time.
 Grid Node List - Required\: A comma-separated list of the CRS nodes. Must be in the format node1-public\:node1-private\:node1-virtual,node2-public\:node2-private\:node2-virtual.
 Interface List - Required\: Comma-separated list of interfaces. Syntax\: "Interface Name"\:"Subnet ID"\:"Public private code" For example\: eth0\:16.78.64.0\:1, eth1\:192.168.1.0\:2
 OCR Devices - Required\: The devices CRS uses to store cluster and database configuration information. The device must have the CRS group, be owned by root, and be at least 256Mb. Must be in the same location as Voting Devices.
 Oracle Inventory - Required\: The location of the system's current Oracle inventory file. If it does not exist, it will be created.
 Scan Info - Required\: The Oracle single Client Access name and port you will use to reference this cluster without specifying a specific node. Example syntax\: sales1-scan.example.net\:1522
 Upgrade to Oracle 12 - 'True' if upgrading an existing Oracle 11g Grid Infrastructure to Oracle 12 Grid Infrastructure, 'False' otherwise. Default is False.
 Voting Devices - Required\: The devices CRS uses to verify cluster node membership and status. The device must have the CRS owner and group and be at least 256Mb. Must be in the same location as OCR Devices.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 CRS Response File - The fully-qualified pathname of the response file to be used by the silent install step.
 Grid Install Option - The Oracle Grid install option specified in the response file. Valid values are HA_CONFIG or CRS_SWONLY.
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.
 e02f0b91-014a-456b-a626-b784d7883d2c.d5c48a85-8049-4fc8-9df4-8d496d633cb6.description=Description\:
 
 This step runs the runcluvfy.sh script found in the CRS installer directory. 
 
 Dependencies\: The step must run as the CRS call wrapper.
 
 Return code\:
 Due to the fact that in certain circumstances the runcluvfy.sh command will incorrectly return failures, this step will always return a 0 if it is able to run the command. Otherwise, the step returns a 1.

Inputs\:
 command - executes RunOracleGridInfrastructurePreInstallationCheck.py
 Call Wrapper - Required\: Jython call wrapper required to run as the CRS owner.
 CRS Binary Stage - Required\: The location where the CRS archive has been (or will be) extracted.
 CRS Group - Required\: The system group to be used by the CRS installation. Typically oinstall.
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Exit Code - Exit code of the step needed for branching.
 e02f0b91-014a-456b-a626-b784d7883d2c.d71b3fdf-b93f-4f72-8eb4-ac58bb7d9640.description=Description\:

This step parses the Oracle inventory files that exists, or else it forwards the inventory information.

(1) If the inventory pointer files are specified and exist, parse these files extracting the contents.
(2) If and inventory file is specified and does not exist, ensure a valid specification.
(3) If no inventory file is specified, assign the appropriate default.

Dependencies\: Must run as the server superuser.

Return Code\: 

0 \= All files were found on the system.
1 \= Errors occured while checking files.

Inputs\:
 command - executes ParseOracleInventory.py
 Inventory Files - Optional\: Comma-separated list of fully-qualified Oracle inventory files. If this parameter is not specified, the workflow looks for the oraInst.loc file in /etc and /var/opt/oracle.
 Oracle Account - Optional\: Oracle user that will own the Oracle Home. This is required only if inventory does not exist.
 Oracle Home - Optional\: The ORACLE_HOME to use if more than one Home is in the inventory file(s).
 Server Wrapper - Required\: String to execute routine as server superuser.
 Server.Become Routine - No description
 host - Target to run this command against
 password - Login information for host
 username - Login information for host
 protocol - ssh/wmi
 timeout - Time (ms) before auto-exit\: use ${ExtendedTimeout} to lengthen.

Results\:
 Cluster Nodes - Comma-separated list of all nodes where the Oracle Home is deployed.
 CRS Account - The OS owner of the ORA_CRS_HOME.
 CRS Active Version - The active CRS version.
 CRS Group - The Oracle group used for the ORA_CRS_HOME installation.
 CRS Home - The last ORA_CRS_HOME location in the inventory file.
 CRS Home Name - The name of the ORA_CRS_HOME as recorded in the inventory.
 CRS Nodes - Comma-separated list of all nodes where the Oracle Clusterware is deployed.
 Inventory Groups - Comma-separated list of fully-qualified inventory groups. One for each Inventory Pointer.
 Inventory Locations - Comma-separated list of fully-qualified inventory pathname directories.

 e02f0b91-014a-456b-a626-b784d7883d2c.description=<pre>
 Purpose

This workflow installs Oracle Grid Infrastructure for a Standalone Server or for a Clustered environment. Once provisioned, the installed Grid Infrastructure provides\:
 -- Oracle Cluster services (SCAN, VIPs, etc...)
 -- Oracle Restart services
 -- The Oracle Listener
 -- ASM storage to databases provisioned on the server


 Dependencies

 -- The workflow must have the unchallenged ability to become the oracle database userid (typically _oracle_).
 -- You must have available a raw disk or partition for ASM to mount.

 Usage Instructions

Review the input parameters listed below, and create a deployment using values appropriate for your environment. This workflow is intended to be run on the target machine where Grid Infrastructure is to be installed.

 Required Inputs

 Server Target - The desired target to run this flow against.
 Server Target Username - The user to login to the Server Target as.
 Server Target Password - The password to login as the Server Target Username.
 Download Source Host - The target host where the files needed for this flow can be downloaded from.
 Download Source Path - The path to where the files can be found on the Download Source Host.
 ASM Diskgroup List - Required\: List of your diskgroup with their associated disk. Example \: DATA(/dev/raw/raw1,/dev/raw/raw2),FLASH(/dev/raw/raw3)
 ASM Groups - Required\: Operating system groups that manage ASM. Syntax\: ASMGroup\:ASMDBA\:ASMOper For example\: oinstall\:dba\:asmuser
 ASM Password - Required\: Password for provisioning an Oracle database using ASM storage. The password used to manage ASM.
 CRS Base - Required\: The location of the Oracle Base directory. This is where the admin directory is located.
 CRS Home - Required\: The location where the CRS software will be installed. The default is /u01/app/oracle/product/12.1.0/grid1
 Oracle Software - Required\: The CRS archive(s) (.zip or .cpio.gz) in the software repository.
 Server.Become Routine - No description

 Optional Inputs

 Clean Code Base - Remove code base from target after execution (True || False).
 Clean JRE - Remove JRE from target after execution (True || False).
 Download From SA - Download binaries from SA (True || False). Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 SA Folder Path - Location of binaries on SA. Must set override for 'SAUser' System Account.
 Debug Level - Set level of output [(least) 1-5 (most)]
 Download Location - Optional\: The directory to which all downloaded files are copied from the software repository. This is only used if the required files are not found on target server but are found in the software repository.
 ASM Disk String - Optional\: Value ASM will use to discover the possible ASM Disks
 Voting Devices - Required\: The devices CRS uses to verify cluster node membership and status. The device must have the CRS owner and group and be at least 256Mb. Must be in the same location as OCR Devices.
 CRS Name - Required\: The unique Oracle name for this CRS cluster. Must contain only letters, numbers, and dashes (-). The default is RAC01
 Network Admin Files - Optional\: Comma-delimited list of files to be downloaded and placed in the CRS_HOME/network/admin directory after the Oracle Software is installed.
 Inventory File - Required\: The location of the system's current Oracle inventory file. If it does not exist, it will be created.
 runInstaller Parameters - Optional\: Parameters to pass to the Oracle runInstaller command such as -force or -ignoreSysPrereqs.
 CLUSTER - Grid Node List - Optional\: Comma-separated list of the Grid Infrastructure nodes. Must be in the format node1-public\:node1-private\:node1-virtual,node2-public\:node2-private\:node2-virtual.
 ASM Redundancy - Optional\: The redundancy level of the ASM disk group. Can be one of the following values\: EXTERNAL for configuring at least 1 ASM disk, NORMAL for configuring at least 3 ASM disks, and HIGH for at least 5 ASM disks. Will be defaulted to EXTERNAL
 Upgrade to Oracle 12 - Optional\: 'True' if upgrading an existing Oracle 11g Grid Infrastructure to Oracle 12 Grid Infrastructure, 'False' otherwise. Default is False.
 Cleanup On Success - No description
 CRS Home Name - Required\: The unique Oracle name for this CRS software install. Must contain only letters, numbers, and underscores (_).
 ASM au_size - Optional\: The allocation unit size of the ASM disk group. Valid values are\: 1, 2, 4, 8, 16, 32, or 64 (MB). The default is 1.
 OCR Devices - Required\: The devices CRS uses to store cluster and database configuration information. The device must have the CRS group, be owned by root, and be at least 256Mb. Must be in the same location as Voting Devices.
 Listener - Optional\: Name and port information of the listener. The syntax is Name\:Port. The default is LISTENER\:1521.
 CRS Response File - Optional\: An OUI (Oracle Universal Installer) response file for this CRS installation to be downloaded from the software respository. If not specified, a default will be created by the workflow for the installation based on a default template. It will be deleted upon completion.
 CRS Group - Required\: The system group to be used by the CRS installation. Must be the primary group of the CRS Account User. Typically "oinstall".
 Ignore System Prerequisites - Set to Y to include the -ignoreSysPrereqs parameter when running the install. Valid values are Y, N, and blank. Blank defaults to N.
 Cleanup On Failure - No description
 CRS User - Required\: The user who will own the CRS software. Typically oracle.
 Extract Location - Optional\: Directory location where the Oracle database software archives will be extracted. Will be cleaned up at end of workflow execution. If not specified, a default will be created.
 CLUSTER - Scan Info - Optional\: The Oracle single Client Access name and port you will use to reference this cluster without specifying a specific node. Example syntax\: sales1-scan.example.net\:1522

 Results Verification

The Console will indicate whether the workflow completed without errors. If all required services are online then your installation was successful.

To further verify the results\:

 1. Set ORACLE_HOME and ORACLE_SID in the terminal(s) for your ASM instance.
 2. crsctl stat res -t
 3. Look at the resources and verify that the required Grid standalone services are online.



 Additional Documentation

Additional information about HP Database and Middleware Automation is available on HP Live Network\:

"http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation"\:http\://hpln.hp.com/group/database-and-middleware-automation

To access the documentation, click the OTHER FILES link and enter your HP Passport credentials.
